    "body": "Closing this PR as we've decided to address this issue at the search client adapter level instead.\n\nThe fix has been implemented in the Searchkit adapter and submitted as a PR: https://github.com/searchkit/searchkit/pull/1412\n\nThe key changes in the Searchkit fix:\n- Added configurable timeout (default 30s) to `ESTransporter` using `AbortController`\n- Modified `@searchkit/instantsearch-client` to return empty results on error instead of throwing, which prevents the infinite re-render loop in InstantSearch\n- Added error result caching to prevent repeated failing requests\n- Added optional `onError` callback for custom error handling\n\nThis approach keeps the error handling closer to the source (the search client) and avoids needing to patch `react-instantsearch-nextjs`. Once the Searchkit PR is merged, users of Searchkit with InstantSearch will get this fix automatically.\n\nThanks @Haroenv for your support and guidance on this issue!",
